<%#
# Number Form Partial

This partial renders an input element for number attributes.
By default, the input is a text field.

## Local variables:

- `f`:
  A Rails form generator, used to help create the appropriate input fields.
- `field`:
  An instance of [Administrate::Field::Number][1].
  A wrapper around the number pulled from the database.

[1]: http://www.rubydoc.info/gems/administrate/Administrate/Field/Number
%>

<div class="field-unit__label">
  <%= f.label field.attribute %>
</div>
<div class="field-unit__field">
  <% if field.attribute == :break_time or field.attribute == :break_sum %>
    <%= f.number_field field.attribute, min: 0, max: 60*24, step: 1, maxlength: 4, required: true %>
  <% elsif field.attribute == :employee_number %>
    <%= f.number_field field.attribute, min: 10000, max: 99999, step: 1, maxlength: 5, required: true %>
  <% else %>
    <%= f.number_field field.attribute, min: 0, step: 1 %>
  <% end %>
</div>
